---
import LegalLayout from "../layouts/LegalLayout.astro";

export const prerender = true;
---

<LegalLayout
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="How devngn.ai handles your data: opt-in, private by design, and yours to delete anytime."
  kicker="Legal"
  updated="June 9, 2026"
>
  <p>
    devngn.ai is built human-first, and that includes your privacy. This policy
    explains what we collect, why, and the control you keep over it. The short
    version: <strong>nothing personal is stored until you opt in</strong>, we read
    your calendar as free/busy only, and you can export or delete everything at any
    time.
  </p>

  <h2>What we collect</h2>
  <p>Only after you explicitly opt in, and only what the feature needs:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Wellness profile</strong>: baseline, preferred intensity, and notes you choose to provide.</li>
    <li><strong>Goals and progress</strong>: the goals you set and the movement breaks you complete.</li>
    <li><strong>Equipment</strong>: the gear you register as available to you.</li>
    <li><strong>Schedule signals</strong>: <strong>free/busy</strong> windows from a connected calendar, or events you push yourself, used to find real gaps.</li>
    <li><strong>Account basics</strong>: an identifier from your sign-in provider so your data is yours.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>What we don't collect</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>We do <strong>not</strong> read the titles, attendees, or contents of your calendar events, only free/busy availability.</li>
    <li>We don't sell your data, and we don't use it for advertising.</li>
    <li>We don't store anything personal before you opt in.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>How we use it</h2>
  <p>
    Your data powers the core experience: detecting genuine gaps in your day,
    tailoring five-second movement prompts to your profile and equipment, and
    tracking streaks, goals, and progress so it's real and reviewable.
  </p>

  <h2>Sharing and social features</h2>
  <p>
    Wellness is better together, but it's opt-in. Goals and streaks are private to
    you unless <strong>you choose</strong> to share them with a team or teammates.
    You control what is shared and can stop sharing at any time.
  </p>

  <h2>Third-party connections</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Calendar providers</strong> (e.g., Google, Microsoft): accessed for free/busy availability only, with your authorization.</li>
    <li><strong>Sign-in</strong>: handled through your chosen provider (such as GitHub) using standard OAuth.</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    These providers process data under their own privacy policies. You can revoke
    their access from your provider's settings at any time.
  </p>

  <h2>Storage and hosting</h2>
  <p>
    Your wellness data is stored in the project's hosted database. The
    <a href="/registry/">vendor registry</a> and marketing pages are public and
    contain no personal data. On the marketing site, local storage is used only to
    remember your light/dark theme preference. That's it.
  </p>

  <h2>Your control</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Export</strong>: you can request a copy of your data.</li>
    <li><strong>Delete</strong>: you can delete all of it whenever you want, and withdrawing consent stops further collection.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Children</h2>
  <p>
    devngn.ai is intended for professional developers and is not directed to
    children under 13. We don't knowingly collect data from children.
  </p>

  <h2>Changes</h2>
  <p>
    If this policy changes, we'll update the "last updated" date above. Significant
    changes will be highlighted where appropriate.
  </p>

  <h2>Contact</h2>
  <p>
    Questions or requests about your data? Reach out via
    <a href="https://davidpine.dev" rel="noopener" target="_blank">davidpine.dev</a>
    or open an issue on
    <a href="https://github.com/IEvangelist/devngn.ai/issues" rel="noopener" target="_blank">GitHub</a>.
  </p>
</LegalLayout>
